The paper deals with semantic segmentation and proposes a new method for instance-level segmentation. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses fully convolutional networks (FCNs) and proposes a new architecture, which suggests that it could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also mentions using a pixel-wise classifier, which suggests that it could belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the paper presents results on both PASCAL VOC and MS COCO datasets, which suggests that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
